    "caption": "Three cards. One continuous painting.\n\nKeiko Fukuyama illustrated Mew, Pidgeot, and Onix as a single panoramic scene for the 1998 Southern Islands set. Place all three side by side and the sky, clouds, and landscape flow without interruption across the borders. The cards were designed to be collected together, not apart.\n\nThe numbers at pokeev.com tell the full story. Mew carries most of the value at $456 raw. Pidgeot sits at $41, Onix at $48. The complete panorama lands at $545 combined. Two of the three are easy to acquire. One is not.\n\nThat gap between the anchor card and its companions is exactly the kind of EV insight pokeev.com is built to surface. Before you buy, build, or sell, run the numbers.\n\nDo you own all three, or are you still hunting the set? Drop a comment below.\n\n#pokemon #pokemontcg #pokemoncards #pokemoncollector #tcg #pokemoncommunity #tcgcollector #pokemoncardgame #tradingcards #cardcollector #pokemoninvesting #pokemonart #pokemonillustration #connectingart #vintagepokemon #pokemonvintage #pokemonpanorama #pokemonuk #pokemoneurope #pokemonusa #pokemonjapan #southernislands #southernislandspokemon #mewpokemon #pidgeot #onix #keikofukuyama #pokemonev #rarepokemoncards #pokemoncardcollection",
